venice.lib.parser

Class XIOParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • venice.lib.parser.XIOParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    XIODomParser, XIORegExParser

    public abstract class XIOParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes classes that provide XIO parsing. Every subclass has to provide methods for parsing from string to event, event to string and preparsing of the timestamp from a string. The preparsing should be faster than the full parsing, but it depends on the implementation of the subclass.

    The strings have to be in the XIO line format.
    Example:
    <sfstring value="hello" timestamp="123" sensorname="testslot"/>

    They should also be able to parse XIO line in old format.
    Example:
    <irio:sfstring value="hello" timestamp="123" sensorname="testslot"></irio:sfstring>

    Subclasses can demand a specific order of the attributes of the XIO lines.

    XIOParser provides a collection of useful static methods to support parsing.

    Author:
    Oliver Eickmeyer

      • INVALID_TIMESTAMP

        public static final long INVALID_TIMESTAMP
        Defines an invalid timestamp.

        For example, methods that parse timestamps into a long value should return this value, if parsing fails (if they do not throw an exception).

      • findSlotLabel

        public static java.lang.String findSlotLabel(java.lang.String s)
        Finds and returns the label of the slot in a sensor name string. Example: In the string test/abc the label of the slot is abc.

        To remember: The sensor name strings (for example in log files) are composed of the namespace label and the slot label. Example: venice/test/abc contains the namespace label venice/test and the slot label abc.

        Note: A well formed sensor name string should never start or end with a slash.

        Parameters:
        s - The string to be searched for the slot label
        Returns:
        • The label of the slot, if found.
        • Empty string, if there is no label after the last slash or if s is an empty string by itself. (Example: test/ leads to an empty string)
        • The input string itself, if there is no namespace label (Example: abc leads to abc)
        • null if s is null.

      • findNamespaceLabel

        public static java.lang.String findNamespaceLabel(java.lang.String s)
        Finds and returns the label of the namespace in a sensor name string. Example: In the string venice/test/abc the label of the slot is venice/test.

        For more information see findSlotLabel.

        Parameters:
        s - The string to be searched for the namespace label
        Returns:
        • The label of the namespace, if found.
        • Empty string, if there is no label before the last slash, or if s does not contain a slash. (Example: abc leads to an empty string)
        • null if s is null.

      • failSlotEvent

        public static SlotEvent failSlotEvent(java.lang.String s)
        Generates a fail slotEvent. A fail slotEvent should be returned by the parser when it fails to parse a string into an event. The value will be the string that the parser failed to parse. The slotlabel will just be "fail" and the timestamp will be set to the value of the INVALID_TIMESTAMP constant.
        Parameters:
        s - The string causing the parser to fail
        Returns:
        a fail slotEvent, containing the parameter s as value, "fail" as slot label, String as type and INVALID_TIMESTAMP as timestamp
